doc.previous: Since 8 May 2007 the liquid restrictions of 100 ml cap is enforced following the 2006 transatlantic aircraft plot Passengers are advised to check in liquids gels and aerosols above 100 ml failing which they will be confiscated by airport security and have to post it back to oneself Anything that is in the security areas is allowed In general practice unacceptable materials are also confiscated and have to post it back to yourself excluding nail clippers nail files umbrellas and racquets
doc.after: Prior to the 1970s American airports had minimal security arrangements to prevent aircraft hijackings Measures were introduced starting in the late 1960s after several high profile hijackings
